   <conbody>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">If auto start is enabled, the system starts
automatically when the <ph platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/ph ">rectifier mains</ph>
               <ph platform="WxW" class="- topic/ph ">DC power supply</ph> returns in case the system
lost all AC and DC power supplies. This can be useful if the system
is located in a remote access location.</p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">To enable/disable auto
start for the system:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Hash key</b> to enter the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b>. </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Use the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Arrow keys</b> to navigate to <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Autostart</codeph>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To enable: </b>Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Clock/number 1 key</b> to turn
on auto start.</p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To disable: </b>Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Star/number 0
key</b> to turn off auto start.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Back key</b> or wait 30 seconds to exit the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b>.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
